            <abstract>
              <p>This document, part of the document 
                  number 7 in Carlo Conti Rossini's edition, 
                  part I of CCR 7 according to Alessandro Bausi's system of reference.
              While there are reasons to consider part I and part II of CCR 7 
              according to Bausi's system of reference as two parts one document, 
              here they are treated as two documents on the basis of codicological 
              disposition and <foreign xml:lang="fr">mise en texte</foreign>.
In this document King Lālibalā's assigns certain lands as gʷǝlts to the 
monastery of Ham. The date noted in the manuscript is 409 year of Mercy, 
which corresponds to <date>1225</date> year of AD. 
                  The document is attested twice, once on the verso of the 
                  folium with a full-page miniature of a temple on the recto, 
                  while writing was evaluated as potentially contemporary 
                  to the actual date mentioned in the document. 
                  Further, without any significant difference, this 
                  document was presumably copied into a small quire, 
                  which  contains a number of documents likely copied 
                  from older documents (originals?) in the sixteenth century.
</p>
            </abstract>
